SIMPLE: regurgitate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Regurgitate
<hw>Re*gur"gi*tate</hw> <pr>(r?*g?r"j?*t?t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[LL. <ets>regurgitare</ets>, <ets>regurgitatum</ets>; L. pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>gurges</ets>, <ets>-itis</ets>, a gulf. Cf.
<er>Regorge</er>.]</ety> <def>To throw or pour back, as from a deep or
hollow place; to pour or throw back in great quantity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Regurgitate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Regurgitate
<hw>Re*gur"gi*tate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be thrown or poured
back; to rush or surge back.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The food may <qex>regurgitate</qex>m the stomach into the
esophagus and mouth.</q> <rj><qau>Quain.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Regurgitation</ent>⟦br⟧
